<subSubSection id="C34AA384FFC2FFEFFF0662DC5FF2F9A7" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFEFFF0662DC5F05FA37" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFF0662DC5DEAFA7F" bold="true" box="[189,498,1420,1447]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
—Species registered only for 
<collectingRegion id="49943EEDFFC2FFEFFCF762DD5FF0FA7F" box="[844,1000,1421,1447]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, particularly in the Serra do Espinhaço region, near the municipality of Barrocão (Fig. 36D). It inhabits rocky savannahs on oxisols with outcrops of rocks on hillsides or roadsides, between 730–1100 meters elevetion.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFEFFF0662A85FA1F983" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFF0662A85DACF9CB" bold="true" box="[189,436,1528,1555]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Conservation status:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFE6B62A95ED6F9CB" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[464,718,1529,1555]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE6B62A95ED6F9CB" box="[464,718,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chamaecrista ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is being considered as “In Danger” (EN, criterion B1, subcriteria b i, ii, v), regarding its conservation, as it was collected in only one location and has small populations (up to 40 individuals) distributed in an area of extension of occurrence of 
<quantity id="4CA85DEAFFC2FFEFFCEC61105FB2F983" box="[855,938,1600,1627]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.155" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="1155.0">1155 m</quantity>
<superScript id="7C255D47FFC2FFEFFC1161105FAAF996" attach="left" box="[938,946,1600,1614]" fontSize="6" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">2</superScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFEFFF0661345FF2F9A7" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" box="[189,1002,1636,1663]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFF0661345DCFF9A6" bold="true" box="[189,471,1636,1663]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Flowering and fruiting:</emphasis>
—It was collected with flower and fruit in July.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34AA384FFC2FFECFF0661D95DDDFE91" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFEFFF0661D95957F97B" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" box="[189,1359,1673,1699]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFF0661D95D50F97B" bold="true" box="[189,328,1673,1699]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFDEF61D95EB6F97B" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[596,686,1673,1699]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFDEF61D95EB6F97B" box="[596,686,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the burnt or “scorched” color of the species stem.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFEFFF0661FC58E3F81B" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFF0661FC5F10F91E" bold="true" box="[189,776,1708,1735]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Morphological relationship and characterization:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFC9F61FD5839F91F" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[804,1057,1709,1735]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFC9F61FD5839F91F" box="[804,1057,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chamaecrista ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recognized by Barneby (1982) as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFE8661815DFCF933" authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby." authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[317,484,1745,1771]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbiculata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE8661815DFCF933" box="[317,484,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. orbiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFDA861815F73F933" box="[531,875,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFDA861815F46F933" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[531,862,1745,1771]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="orbiculata" variety="ustulata">Ch. Orbiculata var. ustulata</taxonomicName>
).
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18DFEFFC2FFEFFCCE61815873F933" author="Mendes, T. P. &amp; Souza, A. O. &amp; Silva, M. J." box="[885,1131,1745,1771]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="159 - 182" refId="ref32727" refString="Mendes, T. P., Souza, A. O. &amp; Silva, M. J. (2020) Molecular phylogeny and diversification timing of the Chamaecrista sect. Absus subsect. Absus ser. Paniculatae, a newly circumscribed and predominantly endemic of the Cerrado Biome group. Phytotaxa 446 (3): 159 - 182. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 446.3.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Mendes 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFC626181580DF933" box="[985,1045,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
based on the results of his phylogenetic study for 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE2E61A55DA4F8D7" box="[405,444,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch.</emphasis>
ser. 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE4361A55E67F8D7" box="[504,639,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Paniculatae</emphasis>
and supported by morphological and geographic evidence, raised 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFA3F61A55D8EF8EB" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="orbiculata" variety="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFA3F61A55CE5F8EB" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. orbiculata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE8760495D8EF8EB" box="[316,406,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE1A60495EB4F8EA" box="[417,684,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">to the species category</emphasis>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFD6060495F70F8EB" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[731,872,1817,1843]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFD6060495F70F8EB" box="[731,872,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18DFEFFC2FFEFFC386049584DF8EB" author="Cota, M. M. T. &amp; Rando, J. G. &amp; Mello-Silva, R." box="[899,1109,1817,1843]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref32369" refString="Cota, M. M. T., Rando, J. G. &amp; Mello-Silva, R. (2020) Chamaecrista (Leguminosae) of the Diamantina Plateau, Minas Gerais, Brazil, with six new species and taxonomic novelties. Phytotaxa 469 (1): 1 - 82. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 469.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Cota 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFC7860495FE7F8EB" box="[963,1023,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFB5E6049596AF8EB" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[1253,1394,1817,1843]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFB5E6049596AF8EB" box="[1253,1394,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym for 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFE9B606D5DDCF88F" authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby." authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[288,452,1853,1879]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbiculata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFE9B606D5DDCF88F" box="[288,452,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. orbiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without commenting on anything precisely and with weak arguments. After permorized analysis of several collections, as well as collections and observations of the taxa now being discussed in their habitats, we realized that 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFEF260D55DCDF847" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[329,469,1925,1951]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFEF260D55DCDF847" box="[329,469,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a set of characters that differentiates it from 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFBAD60D558DCF847" box="[1046,1220,1925,1951]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFBAD60D558D8F847" authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby." authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1046,1216,1925,1951]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbiculata">Ch. orbiculata</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
For this reason, we maintain the same decision made by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC18DFEFFC2FFEFFD9D60F95F17F81B" author="Mendes, T. P. &amp; Souza, A. O. &amp; Silva, M. J." box="[550,783,1961,1987]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="159 - 182" refId="ref32727" refString="Mendes, T. P., Souza, A. O. &amp; Silva, M. J. (2020) Molecular phylogeny and diversification timing of the Chamaecrista sect. Absus subsect. Absus ser. Paniculatae, a newly circumscribed and predominantly endemic of the Cerrado Biome group. Phytotaxa 446 (3): 159 - 182. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 446.3.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Mendes 
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFD3E60F95EA6F81B" box="[645,702,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
in considering both taxa as distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEFF00FFFC2FFECFF06609D5DDDFE91" blockId="57.[136,1452,664,2059]" lastBlockId="58.[136,1451,158,329]" lastPageId="58" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Among the other species studied here, 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFDCF609D5EE6F83F" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[628,766,1997,2023]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ustulata">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFDCF609D5EE6F83F" box="[628,766,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. ustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C508B8CFFC2FFEFFB2E609D595DF83F" authorityName="Mendes &amp; Silva In Mendes et al." authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" baseAuthorityYear="1978" box="[1173,1349,1997,2023]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cercidifolia">
<emphasis id="B9242C1DFFC2FFEFFB2E609D595DF83F" box="[1173,1349,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Ch. cercidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by share setulose branches, including inflorescence axis, external face of the stipules, bracts, bracteoles, sepals and ovaries, and for having two pairs of orbicularis leaflets with inconspicuously prominent tertiary venation. However, they are differentiated mainly by the shrubby habit decumbent in the first and arboreal in the second, pulvinus with 
<quantity id="4CA85DEAFFC1FFECFAF8679259B3FF05" box="[1347,1451,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="cm" value="3.4" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.8">2.8–4 cm</quantity>
long (vs. 
<quantity id="4CA85DEAFFC1FFECFF5567B65D58FED9" box="[238,320,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6 cm</quantity>
long) opaque dark green leaflets with setulose margin (vs. green-bluish leaflets with glabrous margin), panicles 
<quantity id="4CA85DEAFFC1FFECFF50665A5D41FEFD" box="[235,345,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="cm" value="34.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="26.0">26–42 cm</quantity>
long (vs. 
<quantity id="4CA85DEAFFC1FFECFE72665A5E79FEFD" box="[457,609,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9049999999999998" metricValueMax="2.69" metricValueMin="1.1199999999999999" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" unit="cm" value="19.049999999999997" valueMax="26.9" valueMin="11.2">11.2–26.9 cm</quantity>
long) and non-mucronulate anthers (vs. mucronulate), and pubescent fruits (vs. setulose on the margin).
</paragraph>
